children.name: Text
children.value: Meet Dr. Hugo Mercier, the Anarchist. Will he antagonise you, or perhaps become your greatest ally? Discover his unique approach to leadership as you get to know him through his exclusive questline. Advocate for anarchy using his new propaganda articles and items. But beware, there are many downsides to anarchy spreading into your cities...

Dr. Hugo Mercier.

children.name: Text
children.value: Not all players own the required additional content.

children.name: Text
children.value: Select which character you would like to replace with Dr. Mercier.

children.name: Text
children.value: The following additional content is missing:

children.name: Text
children.value: In the Festival of Reason, anarchists come together to celebrate Truth, Liberty, Community and the abolition of Governments.

children.name: Text
children.value: Dr. Mercier's voice drills into the minds of his followers from these towers.

children.name: Text
children.value: You work for something greater now; it's the ultimate blessing I can bestow.

children.name: Text
children.value: Do this your own way— no really! Perceive it in whatever way you wish!

children.name: Text
children.value: A great wave is coming— let it carry you to your dreams.

children.name: Text
children.value: Now's your moment! Action must be taken! Rise! Rise!

children.name: Text
children.value: I can give you the dental key, but you must reach into the mouth and twist.

children.name: Text
children.value: The smallest inkling of success is still your inkling of success!

children.name: Text
children.value: You must be champing at the bit!

children.name: Text
children.value: You've done well. Go now, footloose and fancy-free.

children.name: Text
children.value: You are a doer. Anarchists are doers!

children.name: Text
children.value: A peaceful smile at the end is worth the momentary discomfort.

children.name: Text
children.value: The people love those who make themselves indispensible.

children.name: Text
children.value: You have the courage of your convictions.

children.name: Text
children.value: Instead of dismantling the status quo, you perpetuate it!

children.name: Text
children.value: The chicanery of a career politician.

children.name: Text
children.value: Apathy is the carbuncle of society!

children.name: Text
children.value: And yet the determination comes easily to so many of us!

children.name: Text
children.value: Anyone else would have been able to go through with it.

children.name: Text
children.value: Always try to get at the root of a problem.

children.name: Text
children.value: Success can come in a twinkling of the eye.

children.name: Text
children.value: I find the suspense terrible. Long may it last.

children.name: Text
children.value: The more you do, the more you can do!

children.name: Text
children.value: Keep pushing, never let yourself be pushed back.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your actions urge a final reckoning ever closer, do not relent!

children.name: Text
children.value: There is no right or left, only the liberty of choice!

children.name: Text
children.value: It is not the banner under which you stand, but your equity of spirit.

children.name: Text
children.value: Have you acted on behalf of the people?

children.name: Text
children.value: Your submission carries more weight than any academic paper.

children.name: Text
children.value: I admire your spontaneity, but the occasion is inopportune.

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't enjoy turning away committed activists such as yourself.

children.name: Text
children.value: If you panic, you may have to be killed to save the rest of us.

children.name: Text
children.value: Too many have crossed the line…stabbed us in the back. We have to equalise things.

children.name: Text
children.value: Bad and good sometimes appear to change places, but all will be well if we remember our cause!

children.name: Text
children.value: When love and hope are not enough, I will fight! Die if I have to.

children.name: Text
children.value: It was meant to be Eden before the fall; its pleasures simple, universal, tranquilising.

children.name: Text
children.value: Pamphleteers flood your streets, spreading the good word!

children.name: Text
children.value: A general strike is the people's greatest weapon!

children.name: Text
children.value: The tide turns against you! This is the cusp, the point of no return!

children.name: Text
children.value: Your people, like a wild-eyed mare, are ready to break from their bridle!

children.name: Text
children.value: The people can hold themselves back no longer!

children.name: Text
children.value: They're sick of your tyranny, now that bile is flooding out!

children.name: Text
children.value: They don't need anyone to tell them what to do, look at them!

children.name: Text
children.value: Your dictatorship is over! The people hold the reins now!

children.name: Text
children.value: I didn't set them upon you, I didn’t need to!

children.name: Text
children.value: You were a great help in turning those cultists, you've made a deep connection with my community now.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Pyrphorians are taking vulnerable people away from more constructive forms of resistance.

children.name: Text
children.value: Who are the Pyrphorians, does anyone really know? It's obvious those pulling the strings are fat cats in armchairs living off the chaos and misery.

children.name: Text
children.value: Notice the Pyrphorians wear masks? That's not struggle, that's cowardice.

children.name: Text
children.value: Religion and people's welfare don't mix, just look at the Pyrphorians.

children.name: Text
children.value: If you think neighbouring an anarchist will be chaos, you deceive yourself. Anarchy is order!

children.name: Text
children.value: I challenge you to oversee your own transformation. Don't wait for your people to make it for you!

children.name: Text
children.value: I expect you think you know what anarchy is? Expect to have all those misconceptions overturned!

children.name: Text
children.value: When its this sweet, you have to worry about toothrot.

children.name: Text
children.value: Nothing is more certain than the uncertain!

children.name: Text
children.value: A defining moment, for all of us.

children.name: Text
children.value: This is it, this is change!

children.name: Text
children.value: …and just like that, a thousand poorhouse faces lift.

children.name: Text
children.value: Brave ideas survive through brave individuals like you.

children.name: Text
children.value: You are a mover and shaker.

children.name: Text
children.value: There's a stool for you at the table of the free.

children.name: Text
children.value: How do you feel, to be a salmon leaping upriver?

children.name: Text
children.value: The world must change or be changed!

children.name: Text
children.value: I will never give up on the people.

children.name: Text
children.value: They call it civilisation. It's laughable.

children.name: Text
children.value: Hard to control feelings in times like this.

children.name: Text
children.value: Reduced to serfs in the mud.

children.name: Text
children.value: Well, enjoy the cage you have built for yourself.

children.name: Text
children.value: You think it's free will, but you're a pawn.

children.name: Text
children.value: They feed you lies like a duck seed, and you've never quacked.

children.name: Text
children.value: Perhaps you don't realise what's at stake here!

children.name: Text
children.value: Have you never asked questions? Who doesn't ask questions?

children.name: Text
children.value: You only exist, you're not alive.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't give me that twisted smile!

children.name: Text
children.value: I am Dr. Mercier. Beg pardon, but since I have a foot in your door, you should listen; anarchy is the only way!

children.name: Text
children.value: Dr. Hugo Mercier; shining the lamp that is anarchy into the dark, plaque-ridden crevices of state.

children.name: Text
children.value: Worry not! You've nothing to fear from Hugo Mercier— I am a pacifist. But the people, the people! There is a rampant beast!

children.name: Text
children.value: Take a pamphlet— free as the wind, as we all are!

children.name: Text
children.value: Paradise is all around you, but you really have to look to see it.

children.name: Text
children.value: The island that upset the apple cart.

children.name: Text
children.value: Voice your hate against the state here, without fear of recrimination!

children.name: Text
children.value: This is the crossroads, from which a million starry paths surge in every direction!

children.name: Text
children.value: Say a few words to the people while you're here. Tell them what a lie the government is.

children.name: Text
children.value: I demand so much of them, and yet, if it can free them from their chains…

children.name: Text
children.value: United by suffering; black, white, rich, poor. Our congregation lives and dies together.

children.name: Text
children.value: Unfettered from possessions, they listen only to their hearts...and my broadcasts.

children.name: Text
children.value: The essentials we have in extraordinary abundance. Never a need to look to the outside for aid!

children.name: Text
children.value: They are free now, to sail wherever they wish!

children.name: Text
children.value: No hierarchies aboard my ships. Every man worthy as the next!

children.name: Text
children.value: Like an ocean that collapses petty structures, the people are in heavy swell!

children.name: Text
children.value: Do you not see? The waves rule themselves!

children.name: Text
children.value: It isn't just me who wants to rock the boat.

children.name: Text
children.value: As promised, the masses are provided for!

children.name: Text
children.value: By all means, by all means!

children.name: Text
children.value: In the interest of the people, I accept.

children.name: Text
children.value: My privilege to say no. My right.

children.name: Text
children.value: Only a sheep would baa and nod.

children.name: Text
children.value: As I said to the Queen— no!

children.name: Text
children.value: Why should anarchists all have unruly beards? I shave in solidarity with the workers whose contract obliges it of them! Besides...dentists despise beards.

children.name: Text
children.value: I shepherd no sheep! But stand with them before the fence, ready to leap to liberty!

children.name: Text
children.value: The mouth is a special instrument. In dentistry you see many who cannot play— any tune, let alone one of their own.

children.name: Text
children.value: Only when he came to me with chronic toothache, did the college Dean recognise the impact of dentistry, and reluctantly, offer me a chair.

children.name: Text
children.value: Among the first to be certified a dentist, among the first to label myself "anarchist". Everyday a new first.

children.name: Text
children.value: Being forced to take a trivial position at a trivial institution was humiliating. I could see why the students were so angry.

children.name: Text
children.value: A beautiful gecko came to me, and I knew it was one of those who died wresting the island from the Queen. "Go" I said, "you're free now."

children.name: Text
children.value: Is there a worse thing to give a child than a doll's house? Just because the young Queen used to trap her puppets in them?

children.name: Text
children.value: The wall around us symoblises the world serpent, ouroboros of conciliated paradoxes, self-fertilising, self-sustaining, self-sacrificing.

children.name: Text
children.value: I remember the patients used to lie speechless as they heard my single, simple idea. An idea so big, people called it impossible, but they only lacked the imagination…

children.name: Text
children.value: My accomplishments in dentistry gave me belief. Suddenly I could be as good as anyone—anyone as good as me.

children.name: Text
children.value: Representing the Queen I resigned myself to the jaws of obedience and duty. Then one day, something snapped.

children.name: Text
children.value: Vicente is the vilest of tyrants. But the people of the new world are taking back everything that was never his, as I have, from the Crown.

children.name: Text
children.value: How can George pretend not to hear me when I have a megaphone? Beware! Not all libertarians have open minds!

children.name: Text
children.value: George the "philosopher king," is a liberal sickeningly comfortable in his inertia.

children.name: Text
children.value: Alonso is wild! Absolutely wild. His thirst for violence seems almost unquenchable!

children.name: Text
children.value: Lady Hunt tells me, despite being an enemy of the people, that she had been expecting someone like me to hasten the day of judgement.

children.name: Text
children.value: I, like Bente, am an optimist. To spread absolute love and freedom is the most constructive thing a human can do.

children.name: Text
children.value: I straightened Beryl's jaw, now I expect she wants to straighten mine because I threaten to eradicate poverty forever— thereby destroying her entire premise!

children.name: Text
children.value: Wibblesock, crushed with guilt because he took the money of some undeserving legatee, can you imagine?! I say take that money William! Use it!

children.name: Text
children.value: Von Malching's greed is not impulsive, but compulsive. The difference is night and day!

children.name: Text
children.value: Strip Gasparov's veneer, and there's nothing! Here is a man who pays to have his books riffled, so that his grand library appears well-used!

children.name: Text
children.value: Art is truth. Gasparov is a lie.

children.name: Text
children.value: Jean is one of the finest I know. Using all at his disposal to protect his vision, even if it means contradiction.

children.name: Text
children.value: The plight of that maladjusted and grief-stricken Harlow girl, only excites my desire to prevail against the ruthless machinery of state!

children.name: Text
children.value: Individualists such as Old Nate can always be reminded of the importance of community…

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen chose me, of all people, to mediate with the rioters. I mediated heavily in their favour.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen wanted me for her puppet. But I snipped her strings and gave them to the people!

children.name: Text
children.value: Bleakworth has built a cage around himself. A mercy for the rest of us, he can't see beyond its walls.

children.name: Text
children.value: What more proof than Bleakworth, that virtue and law have nothing in common?

children.name: Text
children.value: Princess Qing is itching to betray her Imperialist heritage, I can sense it.

children.name: Text
children.value: No-one need go cold or hungry.

children.name: Text
children.value: I can fulfil my covenant with the people, now.

children.name: Text
children.value: We never need to import anything, of course.

children.name: Text
children.value: Do not let material things define you!

children.name: Text
children.value: You must understand, I can't promise further trade.

children.name: Text
children.value: If professors only traded ideas as freely as we do...but they only trade in favours.

children.name: Text
children.value: Despite our trade, no hierarchy of property develops here, merely rigourous economic planning.

children.name: Text
children.value: What I like about trading with you, is I know you do it for your people, not just to feed ambition.

children.name: Text
children.value: A free people, with freedom to create beyond imagination built...well...these ships …

children.name: Text
children.value: All I ask is a price per ship that does not shame those who built it.

children.name: Text
children.value: The crown funded these, so be my guest, take as many as you wish!

children.name: Text
children.value: When it comes to ships I have to be unsentimental.

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe I ask too much of these shipbuilders, but see what they had the freedom to author!

children.name: Text
children.value: Think of them not as possessions, but as tools.

children.name: Text
children.value: I have all kinds in store.

children.name: Text
children.value: We have everything we need, though you may not.

children.name: Text
children.value: The price of a good should never exceed its cost.

children.name: Text
children.value: Money will be abolished one day.

children.name: Text
children.value: I know what will be good for you...

children.name: Text
children.value: Who knows where this will lead!

children.name: Text
children.value: The people will not cease until they have abolished you!

children.name: Text
children.value: Anarchy is anything you want it to be.

children.name: Text
children.value: Risk nothing, and you risk everything.

children.name: Text
children.value: Damned if I do, damned if I don't.

children.name: Text
children.value: You think being an anarchist means I'll always disagree?

children.name: Text
children.value: The people trust me to know what's best.

children.name: Text
children.value: No decision is taken without the people's approval.

children.name: Text
children.value: I make up my own rules.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't reduce our bond to a transaction.

children.name: Text
children.value: Stagnation! The tactics of the establishment!

children.name: Text
children.value: Save your filibuster for the royal council!

children.name: Text
children.value: I will not be left to vegetate here!

children.name: Text
children.value: You are not in this wholeheartedly.

children.name: Text
children.value: Everything I demand of you, I demand of myself sixfold.

children.name: Text
children.value: Why not take it even further!

children.name: Text
children.value: I was thinking of something more radical!

children.name: Text
children.value: Even when we yield, we are unyielding.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'll not tarnish my good name with violence.

children.name: Text
children.value: I believe in revolution, not reaction.

children.name: Text
children.value: Throw your bomb if you have the mettle, throw!

children.name: Text
children.value: Then you'll just have to kill the people where they stand.

children.name: Text
children.value: Anarchy, like dentistry, is an exact science.

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't try to lead, I try to be a guide.

children.name: Text
children.value: Once they take hold, ideas become unstoppable.

children.name: Text
children.value: I am agitated, and so are my many friends.

children.name: Text
children.value: You have no authority. No authority!

children.name: Text
children.value: A dentist has to use his drill.

children.name: Text
children.value: War and peace, and in between.

children.name: Text
children.value: You're giving anarchy a bad name.

children.name: Text
children.value: A cross-pollination of our economic principles.

children.name: Text
children.value: We are masters of our own happiness, but we can't do it alone.

children.name: Text
children.value: I can't be seen to be consuming imports.

children.name: Text
children.value: I need the people to help themselves for a while.

children.name: Text
children.value: Economics is too important to be left to the traders.

children.name: Text
children.value: Join the free, live as you please!

children.name: Text
children.value: Not all bonds are bad. Anarchy can also be family.

children.name: Text
children.value: I can only trust myself to do what's right for the people.

children.name: Text
children.value: I have no concerns burning my bridges.

children.name: Text
children.value: Take it. Property is theft, and I practice what I preach.

children.name: Text
children.value: I would give it all away in a moment.

children.name: Text
children.value: The farms have produced so much, I can afford to give some away.

children.name: Text
children.value: Perhaps you should rinse out your mouth!

children.name: Text
children.value: Tyrants always seek to injure the eloquent.

children.name: Text
children.value: And make us all martyrs? So be it!

children.name: Text
children.value: Everyone is ready to sacrifice themselves for anarchy!

children.name: Text
children.value: You and I pursue something beyond ourselves.

children.name: Text
children.value: Nothing in the universe is irreversible.

children.name: Text
children.value: It is a thing both dangerous and adventurous you do!

children.name: Text
children.value: I respect your desire for autonomy.

children.name: Text
children.value: Anarchy means different things to different people.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen took the people's rights, so I took her people.

children.name: Text
children.value: It's so dangerous to go it alone.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't cut yourself off, you'll really regret it.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your first steps towards a gift economy, perhaps?

children.name: Text
children.value: We use what we need and keep the rest for a rainy day.

children.name: Text
children.value: The leader of the Pyrphorians?! I despise organised religion, you should know.

children.name: Text
children.value: Yes, born with privilege, and yet I am willing to sacrifice it— that is the significance of our ideal!

children.name: Text
children.value: I am a contradiction? But we are all contradictions! There is no dovecote to house us all, I nest where I land.

children.name: Text
children.value: It's unnecessary to make sweeping statements about me, I am an enigma you can't solve.

children.name: Text
children.value: You're wrong, in fact I even encourage people to hold two antithetical theories at once.

children.name: Text
children.value: On the contrary, duping the Queen was easy; not once did she and her council envision my betrayal!

children.name: Text
children.value: The people don't need convincing! Or do you not believe the absolute trust they place in me is possible?

children.name: Text
children.value: My friend, people have minds of their own! Any power to persuade I possess, matters little.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't call me a leader. I am an invisible pilot, guiding those most in need.

children.name: Text
children.value: To those who say I have a gift, I say look within yourself, you have it too, but you must allow yourself to nurture it.

children.name: Text
children.value: I resented my father all the years he kept servants! In any case, he will no longer speak to me!

children.name: Text
children.value: No! I seek no special benefits from my position. I own no position!

children.name: Text
children.value: I find comments about my extended family intrusive and deeply offensive.

children.name: Text
children.value: An autocracy? If anything it's the opposite. You have no idea what it is I'm trying to achieve!

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't need a beard! I am a proper anarchist!

children.name: Text
children.value: In pursuit of truth? Yes, it could be said that I am! I didn't know the power of your words could be so incredible.

children.name: Text
children.value: Of course! Ask me anything and I'll tell you, anything at all. I am an open book!

children.name: Text
children.value: Well said. If you do not broadcast your love for your people, it cannot be love!

children.name: Text
children.value: Many of the dentistry students did look up to me, yes, because unlike my peers I gave them the tools to learn.

children.name: Text
children.value: Absolutely! It would have been absurdly easy to have made myself rich plucking teeth for the Queen and council.

children.name: Text
children.value: I see you not as ambitious, but audacious.

children.name: Text
children.value: We can still grow to revere one another.

children.name: Text
children.value: I believe verily, no-one can stop you storming to freedom!

children.name: Text
children.value: The people have great admiration for you.

children.name: Text
children.value: You are finding your own way of thinking.

children.name: Text
children.value: I have to believe human nature is fundamentally good.

children.name: Text
children.value: The best dentists are quick to dispense with theory.

children.name: Text
children.value: You strike me as a typical capitalist.

children.name: Text
children.value: You're an agent of the Queen, don't try to deny it.

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't believe in politics, let alone your politics.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your self-interest puts me in mind of the academy of medicine.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your world seems staid, where is your revolution?

children.name: Text
children.value: You're like everyone else I had to suffer at Archibald's garden parties.

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't think you can recant your statist tendencies.

children.name: Text
children.value: You should be shaking like a wet dog at all the injustice in the world.

children.name: Text
children.value: It's an olig…a federation of like-minds.

children.name: Text
children.value: We all are caught in this maelstrom together.

children.name: Text
children.value: Good to see you promoting solidarity among like-minds

children.name: Text
children.value: The people are sick to the back teeth of your nepotism.

children.name: Text
children.value: The people are reading and hearing all about your collusion.

children.name: Text
children.value: Like whispers under the ivied colonnades, at the despicable high table.

children.name: Text
children.value: The allies of anarchism see through your statist scaremongering.

children.name: Text
children.value: The ulcers of your interventionism are risen again!

children.name: Text
children.value: Pulling the wrong teeth can leave the bloody savour of revolution in the mouth.

children.name: Text
children.value: The enemies of freedom must be coerced!

children.name: Text
children.value: The enemy of the people! Bring the ogre to earth. Destroy them!

children.name: Text
children.value: Anarchy needs firebrands like you, sowing dissent.

children.name: Text
children.value: Spreading corruption among my allies is an attack on the free everywhere.

children.name: Text
children.value: A fellow anarchist has exposed your underhanded imperialism!

children.name: Text
children.value: A spark of mischief in you, I see.

children.name: Text
children.value: Regimes are built on deceit, we have to respond in kind.

children.name: Text
children.value: We all want a share! What's wrong with that?

children.name: Text
children.value: See how the people seize the economy for themselves!

children.name: Text
children.value: Can't you see? I'm breaking the cycle of poverty.

children.name: Text
children.value: A triumph for anarcho-syndicalism! Every honest fellow will have their plot to work on!

children.name: Text
children.value: This land willl forevermore live under the flag of anarchy, and all that promises in the imagination!

children.name: Text
children.value: The greater the divide between rich and poor, the greater the violence will be!

children.name: Text
children.value: Buying your way to a degree, a doctorate, a head of faculty…

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen tried that you know, but the people bought her out! The commoners!

children.name: Text
children.value: A single human soul is worth more than a thousand times what you paid for that island.

children.name: Text
children.value: Usurper! Tyrant! You would seize the economy from the people?!

children.name: Text
children.value: Land and liberty! Each fresh outcrop a barricade against the people's enemy!

children.name: Text
children.value: Not one, but many distinct and autonomous communities!

children.name: Text
children.value: Send in your diggers, apportion each man a square of turf.

children.name: Text
children.value: Feel the soil between your fingers! The earth is a common treasury!

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen wanted to torch our peaceful commune too, but she saw it would only make things worse.

children.name: Text
children.value: We had inspiration to sprinkle over that barren soil, but it's not something you can buy or steal.

children.name: Text
children.value: Perhaps you think that's levelling the land.

children.name: Text
children.value: They create desolation and they call it peace.

children.name: Text
children.value: I am no butcher, and this is no war!

children.name: Text
children.value: My sabre is drawn to the throat of ambition!

children.name: Text
children.value: Shoot then, shoot, what are you waiting for, coward!

children.name: Text
children.value: I pledged to protect the people.

children.name: Text
children.value: Those meaningless deaths are your work.

children.name: Text
children.value: A victory, yet anarchists always remain underdogs!

children.name: Text
children.value: No amount of lives weigh heavier than the cause!

children.name: Text
children.value: If I am ready to die, so should they have been.

children.name: Text
children.value: Ideas always float back to the surface.

children.name: Text
children.value: Better you undergo this procedure without anaesthetic.

children.name: Text
children.value: A tyrant unmasked! Deprived of the sordid accretions of autocratic rule!

children.name: Text
children.value: Death and destruction! Hallmarks of the establishment!

children.name: Text
children.value: The popular tempest has spun, and the flag of anarchy been driven home like a stake!

children.name: Text
children.value: The many headed hydra is decapitated again! This land is claimed for the free!

children.name: Text
children.value: To change the master is not to be free! Those people would rather die than serve you.

children.name: Text
children.value: Only a tyrant! Smearing the walls with blood to eternalise the dreariness!

children.name: Text
children.value: Better to die with dignity renouncing the state; it has failed you, just as much as it has failed your people.

children.name: Text
children.value: You have made a martyr of the people! A martyr of me! My death means the end for you. I'll die happily!

children.name: Text
children.value: How happy and glorious, that you long to reign over us!

children.name: Text
children.value: Just when the people want an enemy, you destroy one of their heroes.

children.name: Text
children.value: By destroying our enemies, we change them…

children.name: Text
children.value: Your victory rouses no leviathan, only the wild and happy monster of freedom.

children.name: Text
children.value: Revolution is no field of clover

children.name: Text
children.value: War can only be defeated through war.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your bomb-builders know there is no other way.

children.name: Text
children.value: Even as a pacifist, I understand and feel where the anger comes from.

children.name: Text
children.value: I have profound dislike for regiments with regalia.

children.name: Text
children.value: Pathetic! There's no bomb better than a book.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your forces are fuelled by chest-thumping jingoism.

children.name: Text
children.value: You don't need to dismember the state to destroy it.

children.name: Text
children.value: You're fighting change, not fighting for it.

children.name: Text
children.value: I require your immediate society, a tyranny is upon us!

children.name: Text
children.value: Time to prove how active you are in the union.

children.name: Text
children.value: The people say I risk it all, praise me for that. Don't you want to be praised?

children.name: Text
children.value: Give them a pistol, I want to see them shoot us both.

children.name: Text
children.value: I hope this is our end; it can be our beginning.

children.name: Text
children.value: They have to believe I'm willing to die for them too.

children.name: Text
children.value: Each man will lay down before you, and die with their eyes to paradise.

children.name: Text
children.value: Row upon row of terro-metallic incorruptibles with the slow-crushing power of a jaguar.

children.name: Text
children.value: Their sacrifice, not any conquest of yours, is what the histories will remember.

children.name: Text
children.value: The plan is they drag you down with them.

children.name: Text
children.value: They feel so strongly you should be dead, I'm not going to stand in their way.

children.name: Text
children.value: It's not a warship. It's a pickaxe for smashing plaster and marble!

children.name: Text
children.value: Too much truth too soon, might stop change from happening.

children.name: Text
children.value: People don't always know what will be good for them in the end.

children.name: Text
children.value: Every student of freedom should at first learn by heart.

children.name: Text
children.value: The truth will out, and your towers will come tumbling down!

children.name: Text
children.value: The kind of nonsense publication professors churn out to keep their comfy chairs.

children.name: Text
children.value: More state lies to subjugate and control!

children.name: Text
children.value: Give them all the truth they can lay their eyes on; pamphlets, posters, pasteboard hats in bold red letters!

children.name: Text
children.value: You are only a messenger. Do not rule like a ruler, and you are blameless. You are immune!

children.name: Text
children.value: Make no illusions; what you are asking of them is difficult, it takes courage.

children.name: Text
children.value: Farmers, miners, bakers free to intermingle, to share and celebrate their expertise!

children.name: Text
children.value: The cyclidion where the winds of change swirl and crystallise into ideas more radiant than any gemstone.

children.name: Text
children.value: Where the brain finds irrigation, where every seed of thought is shared and fostered to bloom.

children.name: Text
children.value: The stream flows to the sea, you cannot stem it, only divert it, and it will arrive there in the end.

children.name: Text
children.value: Let them march, let them egg the police, there's no stopping the unstoppable!

children.name: Text
children.value: No power is legitimate, but the irrepresible power of the people!

children.name: Text
children.value: Your workers understand the need to work hard, don't patronise them.

children.name: Text
children.value: Anarchy is all for them, your humble worker, I will ensure their suffering is soon at an end.

children.name: Text
children.value: The cyclidion where the winds of change swirl and crystallise into ideas more radiant than any gemstone.

children.name: Text
children.value: Where the brain finds irrigation, where every seed of thought is shared and fostered to bloom.

children.name: Text
children.value: Production should exist to meet human needs, nothing more!

children.name: Text
children.value: Clothes should not be worn as marks of status!

children.name: Text
children.value: Each a juju of state control; of mind control!

children.name: Text
children.value: I believe the leaf-rollers among the most enlightened of all workers.

children.name: Text
children.value: When people are starving, why turn your nose up at the potato?

children.name: Text
children.value: Dress as one, but think apart!

children.name: Text
children.value: Your unblinking, red-eyed dogs emerge to sweep your city of its soul.

children.name: Text
children.value: I am helping to build a society that polices itself.

children.name: Text
children.value: What right do those idiots have to tell the people what to think, who to be, what to do?

children.name: Text
children.value: Trinkets and baubles which foster and perpetuate greed and inequality!

children.name: Text
children.value: Cultural segregation; another red rag to the real people!

children.name: Text
children.value: Shop windows to the unattainable; the capitalist illusion of happiness.

children.name: Text
children.value: Lazy workers never find the strength to resist, do they?

children.name: Text
children.value: Idleness is a symptom of conformity, of acceptance of the unacceptable!

children.name: Text
children.value: People are happy to work hard when they know what they're working for.

children.name: Text
children.value: I push the people no harder than I push myself; day and night.

children.name: Text
children.value: Start telling the truth, or you'll cause yourself a lot of pain.

children.name: Text
children.value: Word of mouth isn't enough, but I think you know that.

children.name: Text
children.value: If you won't sell anarchy, you must be against it!

children.name: Text
children.value: Your people can finally read all the truth you've been keeping from them!

children.name: Text
children.value: Anarchy spreads by way of your pamphlets!

children.name: Text
children.value: The word of anarchy taking wing! No more lies!

children.name: Text
children.value: Take them in at your own risk— I have my spies.

children.name: Text
children.value: Of course they'll pretend they're desperate to be rescued, just like the others...

children.name: Text
children.value: Some of those bad eggs are still good...

children.name: Text
children.value: Rebel against your complacent heritage, feed your company to the lions.

children.name: Text
children.value: I pulled Lord Ditchwater's teeth, he never showed remorse for the closures of the mines, and the desolation of that island.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Monarch commanded me to placate the mob, instead I stirred them up!

children.name: Text
children.value: Use whatever means you can to overthrow the system. Even the system itself.

children.name: Text
children.value: If you need a target for your anger, its obvious who the enemy is here.

children.name: Text
children.value: The state wrongfully imprisoned your father. You should be angry. You should do something.

children.name: Text
children.value: The New World is a cradle of anarchism, it's important for me to include its pockets of resistance in our federation.

children.name: Text
children.value: Use the Queen to drive your own agenda, that's what I did.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Pyrphorians are just another sheep cult.

children.name: Text
children.value: The business with Prosperity is a perfect example of the ruination of the individual by the state.

children.name: Text
children.value: If the monarch now judges the people, then it's time the people judged the monarchy.

children.name: Text
children.value: Edvard's fate should rest in the hands of those he hurt, instead of those ignorant wigs.

children.name: Text
children.value: Even if they are just a mindless cult, the same feelings are shared by so many.

children.name: Text
children.value: Why the need for the masks? That's what I can't understand.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Pyrphorians are gone, but the problem that caused them, absurd crown on her head, is somehow still there.

children.name: Text
children.value: Think it will be so easy to slip back into comfortable old ways? Think again.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm shining my spot lamp on your face, I can see you but you can't see me.

children.name: Text
children.value: I out them publicly, spies, so the people can pick their fate.

children.name: Text
children.value: I have a mouth mirror and a headlamp, you can't hide your cavities from me.

children.name: Text
children.value: You find all kinds lurking between your gnashers.

children.name: Text
children.value: A two-facedness I've rarely seen beyond the quads of colleges.

children.name: Text
children.value: How can the oppressed have secured the island of a Queen without some subterfuge?

children.name: Text
children.value: Discretion is a temporary necessity, in future, all will be out in the open!

children.name: Text
children.value: Proud vigilantes who run the tunnels without any word from me.

children.name: Text
children.value: Sometimes when a dentist rummages in your mouth, talking in code, you don't need to know why.

children.name: Text
children.value: Someone has betrayed the commune. That's very serious.

children.name: Text
children.value: Machines shall one day disencumber every worker!

children.name: Text
children.value: Wholesome statistics and mechanisms! Not the mendacious toffees of state our parents ply us with.

children.name: Text
children.value: A real dentist for example, needs only a few simple tools.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your transformation needs courage, not rational thought.

children.name: Text
children.value: Within these walls, you are free. No-one outside can say the same.

children.name: Text
children.value: We need our defences. Our idea is precious, give everything to defend it.

children.name: Text
children.value: Wherever you go, whomever you meet, cherish truth, defend it fiercely.

children.name: Text
children.value: The world out there hates you. It's filled with death and bad people who want to hurt you.

children.name: Text
children.value: You are all free to leave at any time, but then, who would want to? We have it all here.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some of you have called me Messiah. I ask you to stop. I am no more special than any of you.

children.name: Text
children.value: There will be spies among us. Treat them without hostility— have faith they will get better soon.

children.name: Text
children.value: Hysteria is the enemy. Divert your passion into action against our common enemy.

children.name: Text
children.value: We may come under siege at a moment's notice. Be ready to act precisely as we have planned.

children.name: Text
children.value: Any person or persons possessed of contraband should be reported at once.

children.name: Text
children.value: I need you to keep producing for me. We're going to need to stockpile as much as we can.

children.name: Text
children.value: The amnesty is necessary. The weapons are not being confiscated, but put within everyone's reach.

children.name: Text
children.value: Anyone who disagrees, I invite to talk with me in person, so your concerns can be dealt with.

children.name: Text
children.value: Assure yourselves, we are investigating the recent disappearances.

children.name: Text
children.value: We have to be brutal. The world out there is more brutal than any of you know.

children.name: Text
children.value: Species Unrecorded. This species has not yet been categorised, why not name it after yourself!

children.value: Watasenia scintillans. Very small, it uses counter-illumination to hide from predators, mimicking the surface water color.

children.name: Text
children.value: Atractosteus spatula. The species has existed for more years than a person could count in their lifetime.

children.name: Text
children.value: Centrophryne spinulosa. A deep-dwelling anglerfish whose lantern lights prey that it minces with its many recurved teeth.

children.name: Text
children.value: Mitsukurina owstoni. Captures the imagination with its extensive proboscis, much like the mythical goblin Tengu.

children.name: Text
children.value: Chiasmodon niger. Stuffs prey larger than itself into a stretchable cocoon-like basket that dangles from its belly.

children.name: Text
children.value: Cyanea capillata. The rapunzel of the sea, this great hairy stinger can grow longer even than the blue whale!

children.name: Text
children.value: The legendary Kraken, captured! It propels itself wildly around the tank! Tiny human observers cower under its mesmerising gaze!

children.value: Latimeria chalumnae. Old Nate looks at you and says this isn't the only living fossil hanging around the sea bed.

children.name: Text
children.value: Awarded to an unknown sailor for bravery in a previous arena.

children.name: Text
children.value: This well-preserved sculpture once led from the prow at the battle of Trelawney.

children.value: The colourful and talismanic bust that fronted one of the great ships that sank at Trelawney.

children.name: Text
children.value: A fine military decoration of an experienced campaigner present at the battle of Trelawney.

children.name: Text
children.value: The great strategist's blade. Last seen aloft and glinting in the southern sun, just before the fleet cut through the enemy line.

children.name: Text
children.value: A remarkable figurehead belonging to a resplendent imperial ship that fought in the battle of Trelawney.

children.name: Text
children.value: Nadasky's dying wish was that this medal be recovered for his young son, who dreamed of becoming an admiral like his father...

children.value: A remarkable figurehead belonging to a magisterial La Corona ship that sank at the battle of Trelawney.

children.name: Text
children.value: Evidence of a long-lost civilisation? They say the Kingdom of Atlantis spanned a vast and fertile continent that, according to legend, tragically subsided into the sea.

children.name: Text
children.value: This sunken shrine to fork-wielding Poseidon seems ironic now. Why did Poseidon not save his children, when the oceans were his to command?

children.name: Text
children.value: No courthouse could bridle the hubris of the Atlanteans, and so it was left to the fates intead to condemn those peoples to the eternal abyss.

children.name: Text
children.value: A statue cut in a material so rare that for millennia it has been known only by its name. It is quite possible that this is the only example of that mineral remaining in nature.

children.name: Text
children.value: The megalithic structure lends further credence to the existence of a lost continent to the west. Experts say this stepped pyramid could have been at the heart of Atlantean ritual.

children.name: Text
children.value: A tablet so mystifying it will convince the vast majority of museum visitors Atlantis existed, while leaving true scholars of the ancient world pretty skeptical.

children.name: Text
children.value: Old Nate quirkily affixed a moon pool to the base of this diving bell, enabling better access to the abyss.

children.name: Text
children.value: Old Nate's proudest work; a controlled flow of gas sent via its umbilical cable enables this bell to dive deeper than ever before.

children.name: Text
children.value: Old Nate's first attempt to map the depths using sound.

children.name: Text
children.value: An improved version of Old Nate's echo-ranger, with more bells and whistles.

children.name: Text
children.value: Sound out the most sunken of sunken treasures with this subsurface detector— an innovation in sea surveying far ahead of its time.

children.name: Text
children.value: A new standard in diving cables.

children.name: Text
children.value: The elasticity of these cables allow for more flexibility in the bell's carry weight.

children.name: Text
children.value: Nate's most cunning cabling, durable under heavy loads and supporting a variety of systems between the diving bell and its parent.

children.name: Text
children.value: Brings scores of fascinating marine creatures to the surface.

children.name: Text
children.value: Has the miraculous power to draw the most bizarre abyssal creatures in creation to the surface.

children.name: Text

children.name: Text
children.value: A reinforced variant, which in spite of the minor combustion risk, takes all the labour out of warehouse work.

children.value: Old Nate's baby. Prone to the odd tantrum, but providing the lift everyone needs in times of logistical disconsolation.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some say there is a tiny boy inside pulling the levers.

children.name: Text
children.value: Compensates for its faithfulness in performing simple human tasks by being wilfully blind.

children.name: Text
children.value: The nearest thing Nate has to a companion. Unlike a human servant, it won't complain when he kicks it for setting things on fire.

children.name: Text
children.value: So the blue cable to the yellow pin... Oh wait... Was it red?

children.name: Text
children.value: The persistent screech this extra-powerful contraption generates cannot be normal...

children.name: Text
children.value: The enthusiast's choice. Old Nate neglected to include an operating manual, meaning there's the chance of the odd accident.

children.name: Text
children.value: Makes holes in people so their souls may escape.

children.name: Text
children.value: "Don't blame me, I just make 'em! I'm not the one pulling the trigger..."

children.name: Text
children.value: Even Old Nate seems to regret having begat a monster so mean and metallic— that's why he'll only give it to people he trusts.

children.name: Text
children.value: Grab even more with each fell swoop.

children.name: Text
children.value: These tricky lobster nippers could sneak mice out from their slippers, or tip some salted kippers on some drippy tallship skippers.

children.name: Text
children.value: Clever use of water's potential energy generates electricity.

children.name: Text
children.value: This advanced hydroelectric paddlewheel is immune to rust and corrosion, if not the odd explosion.

children.name: Text
children.value: This unique hydroelectric generator has a gold plaque inscribed with its inventor's motto; "Consequences be dammed! Ha! — N8"

children.name: Text
children.value: A double-barreled cannon that loads itself, and more worryingly, chooses targets itself...

children.name: Text
children.value: Self-loading twin barrel cannon with added vim! Simply point in the approximate direction of the enemy, and let her rip!

children.name: Text
children.value: Old Nate has only just realised the destruction this double-barreled beast is capable of. A hint of regret? Naahh, can't be...

children.name: Text
children.value: A lively auxilliary propeller that can be attached to any sea-going vessel.

children.name: Text
children.value: The 'Cyclone' has several advantages over the 'Squall', with an enlarged inlet cowl, and better quality materials.

children.name: Text
children.value: It wasn't built for water, but having rescued the mighty propeller from a crashed zeppelin, Nate thought 'why not?'

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe first designed to make car races, who knows.

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe first designed to make car races, who knows.

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe first designed to make car races, who knows.

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe first designed to make car races, who knows.

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe first designed to make car races, who knows.

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe first designed to make car races, who knows.

children.name: Text
children.value: Blows up one in every ten passing ships (probably).

children.name: Text
children.value: Bigger and prongier. Adds a bit of froth and fizz to the mix whenever its destructive services are called upon.

children.name: Text
children.value: A mine of monstrous size and ferocity, whose horns really hertz. Look close and you can see steam puffing from its wetted nostrils.

children.name: Text
children.value: These modified fireworks are certainly going to excite in one way or another...

children.name: Text
children.value: A highly experimental batch of fireworks likely to cause pleasure and pain in equal measure.

children.name: Text
children.value: If they are anything like the batch Nate prepped for the late King's Golden Jubilee, this shall be a night to glow long in the memory.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Small Gold Ore Finder

children.name: Text
children.value: Increases your prospects of striking gold.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Medium Gold Ore Finder

children.name: Text
children.value: A bit of hip-wiggle in this iteration seems to attract even more gold.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Big Gold Ore Finder

children.name: Text
children.value: This model is the gold standard. Simply pour black gold in and get gold gold out.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Small Copper Ore Finder

children.name: Text
children.value: A sideline in copper and zinc.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Medium Copper Ore Finder

children.name: Text
children.value: A proper cropper of zinc and copper.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Big Copper Ore Finder

children.name: Text
children.value: One of Old Nate's more down-to-earth inventions. Gathers precious metals at a remarkable rate.

children.name: Text
children.value: Makes sure not a drop goes to waste.

children.name: Text
children.value: Gathers fossil goop the average sucker might miss.

children.name: Text
children.value: Only five star crude will pass this extractor's exacting selection process.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Ancient Trade Route Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map marks the lost ruins of a small village in the Old World.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Ancient Trade Route Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map signals the location of an ancient trading post in the New World.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Ancient Trade Route Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map will lead you to the remains of an abandoned ship near Cape Trelawney.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Lost City Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: The people who built this temple couldn't have foreseen the catastrophe that drove their place of worship to the bottom of the sea.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Lost City Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: No one knows who built this pyramid, or how it sank to the bottom of the ocean.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Lost City Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map reveals the place where a thriving city once stood, now resting below the surface.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Legendary Site Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: The pleasure palaces of Baiea were pulled under the sea, along with their owners' luxuries and excesses.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Legendary Site Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map seems to signal the entrance to the legendary lost city of Paititi, but nobody has yet been able to find it...!

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Legendary Site Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A cartographer and linguist studied this ancient manuscript to produce a map to the legendary city of Atlantis.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Rare Fishes Distribution Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map will lead you to uncover the rare species tangled in the kelp forest.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Rare Fishes Distribution Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: The rich fauna of the seagrass meadow awaits you where the X marks the spot.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Rare Fishes Distribution Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map will lead you to a coral garden and all the different species that thrive in it.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Threatened Animals Sanctuary Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: Some of the mysterious species that roam the depths of this oceanic trench haven't yet been discovered.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Threatened Animals Sanctuary Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: This map marks one of the richest ecosystems in the planet.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Threatened Animals Sanctuary Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: It's hard to believe that some of these creatures truly exist, and are not the stuff of dreams — or nightmares.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Mythological Animal Hideout Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: It is hard to believe that this map will lead you to the colossal serpent deity, but the myths must have stemmed from something...

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Mythological Animal Hideout Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: Could this really be the place where the Huacan god rests...?

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Mythological Animal Hideout Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: Multiple sightings confirm that this may be the best place to capture the legendary Kraken — or be captured by it.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Naval Battles Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A map of a big seafight that occurred in home waters recently. Some machines may still be at the bottom of the sea.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Naval Battles Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A map of a big seafight that occurred abroad recently. Some machines may still be at the bottom of the sea.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Naval Battles Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A map of a big seafight that occurred at Trelawney recently. Some machines may still be at the bottom of the sea.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Merchant Ships Sinking Spots Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A very rare map indicating the shipwreck location of a wealthy merchant ship in home waters.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Merchant Ships Sinking Spots Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A very rare map indicating the shipwreck location of a wealthy merchant ship in waters abroad.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Merchant Ships Sinking Spots Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A very rare map indicating the shipwreck location of a wealthy merchant ship in the waters of Trelawney.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Royal Shipwreck Map (Old World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A unique map marking the location of Willie's special fortune. If there's anything down there, it will surely be of high value.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Royal Shipwreck Map (New World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A unique map marking a vault of contingencies for Isabel's rebels. If there's anything down there, it will surely be of high value.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Royal Shipwreck Map (Sunken World)

children.name: Text
children.value: A unique map marked with the wreck of Vicente's favourite ship. If there's anything down there, it will surely be of high value.

children.name: Text
children.value: Knows what to look for, and how and where to look.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Doctor Croft, the Fearless Submarine Archaeologist

children.name: Text
children.value: If there's a chance of recovering the past, she'll be the first to dive in.

children.name: Name
children.value: item fluff Flinders Petrie, the Pioneer of Preservation of Artefacts

children.name: Text
children.value: Said to vomit at the sight of soot, Flinders' passion for keeping immaculate exhibits is both his gift and his curse.

children.name: Text
children.value: He'd like to be beneath the sea.
